      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GIRL GOES ZIP (6) box seated before sticking on well to finish 6 lengths away in third (16.12) at this track in a Grade 5 over 272m. Has good early speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Top chance in this line up. IRON LADY (1) was safely held last time out, finishing sixth at Maitland over 400m behind Special Style (22.96) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to her credit. Can measure up this time. COCO BELLA (7) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing seventh (23.54) in a Grade 5 at this track. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Worth another chance. HI LO RAIN (4) is a chance after four-and-a-half months.",
